This paper discusses statistical tests for random number generators, which falls under the category of probability and statistics (cs.PR). It also discusses flaws in these generators, which could be considered a form of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves analyzing and manipulating data, which could fall under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper proposes improvements to the generators, which could fall under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
